cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PlantDx, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "PlantDx: A Knowledge-Grounded Framework for Instruction-Tuning Datasets for Agricultural Vision-Language Models"
abstract: >-
  PlantDx is a reproducible, knowledge-grounded framework for constructing
  instruction-tuning datasets for agricultural Vision-Language Models. Captions
  are generated from a curated, cited Disease Knowledge Base and a controlled
  vocabulary via ontology-driven templates and multi-stage validation, without
  using any VLM/LLM prediction or image analysis.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "PlantDx Contributors"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/iAakash1/experimentation"
keywords:
  - vision-language models
  - instruction tuning
  - plant pathology
  - agriculture
  - knowledge-grounded generation
  - QLoRA
  - MLX
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-11"
